name: Douglas Brose
biography: Douglas Santos Brose (Cruz Alta, December 11, 1985) is a Brazilian karateka, considered by many the greatest Brazilian karate fighter of all time. It is sponsored by Arawaza by the Federal Government and the state of Santa Catarina.Edgar Ferraz, former president of the CBK, Douglas Brose is 'the greatest athlete medalist and lead the Brazilian karate of all time'. He participated in the Pan American Games in Rio de Janeiro in 2007 and Guadalajara in 2011, being placed third and obtaining the bronze medal in both competitions. In 2015 he became champion of the Pan American Games in Toronto in Canada. In 2009, he won the gold medal at the World Games in Kumite category up to 60 kg. In the World Games, 2013 in Cali, ranked second with a silver medal. In October 2013, won the bronze medal at the World Combat Games in the same category. In 2008 she won her first bronze medal in the senior world championship in 2010, won the gold medal at the World Karate AchievementHeader in 2012 and won his 3rd medal in world championships in Paris. In 2014 it was again world champion in Bremen, Germany, by winning the Dutch Geoffrey Berens.

name: Amir Mehdizadeh
biography: Amir Mehdizadeh is an iranian karateka who was proclaimed world champion in Paris in 2012 and won the bronze medal at the next world championship in Bremen in 2014. In 2015 was proclaimed asian champion in Yokohama.

name: Angelo Crescenzo
biography: Angelo Crescenzo born on August 5, 1993 in Sarno, Italy. He is an italian karateka who was proclaimed World Champion in Madrid on 10 November 2018 and won the silver medal at European Championships celebrated on 2018.

name: Matias Gomez
biography: Matias Gomez was born on July 22, 1990 in Ciudad Real. When he was 17 years old, he was proclaimed world champion in the cadet category. Soon I got a scholarship to study and train in Madrid high performance center. When he was 19 years old win his first senior international medal, win bronze medal in world championship in Belgrade 2010. In 2012 proclaimed champion of Europe in Tenerife, Spain.

name: Magdy Hanafy
biography: Magdy Hanafy is an Egyptian karateka who was proclaimed world champion in Paris in 2012 and won the silver medal at the next world championship in Bremen in 2014.

name: Burak Uygur
biography: Burak Uygur (born April 14, 1995) is a European Games champion Turkish karateka competing in the Kumite 67 kg category.He is a member of İstanbul Büyükşehir Belediyesi S.K. He is one of the promises of present and the future.

name: Steven Da Costa
biography: Steven Da Costa (born January 23, 1997) is a European Games vice-champion french karateka competing in the Kumite 67 kg category. He is one of the promises of present and the future.

name: Jordan Thomas
biography:
Jordan Thomas (born 1992) is a European and World Champion English karateka. He is the son of William Thomas, a European and World Karate Champion.
Training with the Kaizen Karate Federation, he became in 2014 the 67kg Senior European Karate Champion after defeating Aliyev Niyazi from Azerbaijan in the final in Tampere, Finland.
At the 2016 World Karate Championships in Linz, Austria Thomas took gold in the Kumite -67 kg weight, and became the Kumite -67kg World Karate Champion.

name: Rafael Aghayev
biography:
Rafael Aghayev is the first karateka to be a 5-time individual world champion, a record he achieved at the World Championships in 2016 in Linz.
Rafael Agayev was born on March 4, 1985 in the city of Sumgait. He began to play football and study karate at the age of 7 with his first master Rafael Mamedov.
In 2007 Rafael graduated from the Azerbaijan State Academy of Physical Culture and Sports, Single combat sports Faculty, chair of “Fight and its methodology”, degree of coach and master in karate. From 2007 to 2008 Rafael passed military service in Agjabedi region of Azerbaijan Republic. After it he was transferred to the Central Sports Club of the Ministry of Defense. At the first national competitions, he was noticed and invited to train in one of the most famous sports clubs of the Republic.

name: Luigi Busa
biography: Luigi Busa born in 1987 , avolese practitioner since 1993, always with the company 'Association Martial Arts Amateur Sports Centre', affiliated to the FIJLKAM ( Italian Federation Judo Karate Martial Arts ) with the rank of black belt 5th Dan awarded by competitive merits , in 2003 he made his first entry into the Italian National Youth and became owner and captain. In his career, always trained by his father Nello, today obtained the following sports results within the Federation.

name: Stanislav Horuna
biography: Stanislav Horuna was born on March 1, 1989 in Ukraine. He belongs to the most important Ukrainian karate club, Sportskarate.ua UNION . In 2014 He won bronze medal in world championships and silver medal in European Championships.

name: Tom Scott
biography: Tom Scott was born on January 9, 1990 in Texas. He practice Wado Ryu karate style, he is Pan American Champion and Pan American Gold Medalist. Tom Scott is the first American to win the Paris Open in 16 years. (Only two Americans have ever taken gold). Two medals at the Pan American Games makes Tom the second most decorated karate athlete of all time for Team USA Olympic events.

name: Noah Bitsch
biography: Noah Bitsch was born on September 29, 1989 in Vienna. He starts in the discipline Kumite 75kg. At its biggest sporting successes include 2nd at the World Games 2013 ( -75kg ) and the victory at the 2012 European Championship team, and the Vice World Champion title in 2014 with the team.

name: Ugur Aktas
biography: Ugur Aktaş (born October 10, 1995) is a European champion Turkish karateka competing in the kumite -84 kg division. He is two times European Champion at European Championships 2016 in Montpellier (France) and 2017 in Kocaeli (Turkey).

name: Kenji Grillon
biography: Kenji Grillon (born October 28, 1989) is a French karateka. He awarded the 1st Dan in Karate and is two-time world champion and European champion in Kumite. Kenji Grillon has already started as a child with the Karate Sport. Early on he had first success in the competition. After he was appointed in 2005 in the French national youth team, he had on his first international success in the year. On November 25, 2012 he was the world champion to 84 kilograms in Paris his greatest success. In the final at the Paris Palais Omnisports he fought before 14,000 spectators against the Japanese Ryutaro Araga he beat clear. On the same day he was also world champion in the team with the French national team. In May 2013 he became European champion in Kumite in the weight category to 84 kg Budapest. On October 21, 2013 he defeated in the finals of the World Combat Games in St. Petersburg, in turn, the Japanese Ryutaro Araga with 1: 4 and grabbing himself the gold medal in the weight category to 84 kg. When WKF Karate World Cup in 2014, he could not participate as a defending champion. He paused at the Paris Open 2014 feet.

name: Ryutaro Araga
biography: Ryutaro Araga (October 16, 1990) is a japanese karateka. He is brother of Tomoko Araga who was world champion 2006 in Finland. They train Goju Ryu style in the dojo Ara Kaya in Kameoka City, Kyoto. Ryutaro Araga has twice been silver medal in the World Championships and twice gold medal in the Asian Championships.

name: Gogita Arkania
biography: Gogita Arkania is a Georgian karateka born on May 2, 1984, in Ochamchire, Georgia. After several bronze medals in European Championships and World Championships in 2014 he got his crowning achievement of his career proclaimed champion of the world in Bremen.

name: Stefano Maniscalco
biography: Stefano Maniscalco is a italian karateka was born in 12 May, 1982 in Palermo. Maniscalco is World and European Champion, he won his first senior international medal in 2001 in Sofia when he was 19 years old.

name: Enes Erkan
biography: Enes Erkan (10 May 1987 Sakarya) , Turkey karate . 2012 World Karate Championships held in the men's Kumite in Paris , +84 kg final of the Azerbaijani Shahin faced with Atamov Erkan was the gold medal by defeating his opponent 3-0 . name: Jonathan Horne
biography: Jonathan Horne (born January 17, 1989 in Kaiserslautern) is a German karateka. He wears the third Dan Shotokan, World Games winner was 2005 Junior World Champion (+75 kg), Team Vice World Champion 2014, 2009 (+80 kg) and 2013 (+84 kg) and many times european champion. He was awarded the Silver Laurel sheet and applies according Karate Records as the best karateka in the world (+ 84 kg WKF).

name: Sajad Ganjzadeh
biography: Sajad Ganjzadeh (born January 4, 1992) is a Iranian karateka who was proclaimed world champion in Linz in 2016 in the Kumite +84 kg weight

name: Miho Miyahara
biography: Miho Miyahara born on September 3, 1996 in Japan. She is a Japanese karateka who was proclaimed World Champion in Madrid on 10 November 2018 and won the silver medal at World Championships celebrated on 2016.

name: Serap Ozcelik
biography: Serap Özçelik (born February 18, 1988 in Istanbul, Turkey) is a Turkish female karateka competing currently in the Kumite -50 kg division. She is twice European champion and the first gold medalist in the European Games. She began with Karate sport in 2000 at the age of twelve in Güler Spor at Eyüp, Istanbul. In 2005, Özçelik was admitted to the national team, and competed in all age categories for her country. She is a member of EGO Sport Club in Ankara. Özçelik serves as a teacher of physical education in Yaşar Doğu Primary School in Kağıthane, Istanbul.

name: Alexandra Recchia
biography: Alexandra Recchia, born October 25, 1988 in Lyon (Rhone) 1 is a French karateka best known for winning the test of women's individual Kumite below 50kg championships Karate World 2012 in Paris, France.

name: Bettina Plank
biography: Bettina Plank is an Austrian karate born on 20 February 1992 in Feldkirch. She has been European champion since her kumite victory under 50 kilograms at the 2015 European karate championships in Istanbul.

name: Sara Cardin
biography: Sara Cardin is a italian karateka born on January 27, 1987 in Conegliano .She is world champion 2014 in Bremen and european champion 2016 in Montpellier in category less than 55 kg.

name: Anzhelika Terliuga
biography: Anzhelika Terliuga (born March 23, 1992) is a Ukrainian karateka competing in the kumite 55 kg division. She is multiple European champion and medalist.

name: Emily Thouy
biography: Emily Thouy is a French karateka born on January 26, 1993 in Clichy .She is world champion team in the 2012 World Karate Championships in Paris and won silver medal the 2013 Karate European Championships in Budapest in Kumite team. Individual silver medal in Kumite less than 55 kg championships Karate World 2014 in Bremen , she then won the gold medal in individual Kumite 55kg less the Karate European Championships 2015 in Istanbul. It won gold medal in individual European Games 2015 in Baku.

name: Jelena Kovačević
biography: Jelena Kovačević, born on November 16 1984 in Opatija, Croatia is a karateka. It is European champion in Kumite under 55kg karate championships of 2009 and 2012. Europe is also vice-world champion in the same category championships Karate World 2012 in Paris, France.

name: Giana Lotfy
biography: Gianna Lotfy is an Egyptian karateka who was proclaimed world champion in 2014 at the age of 20 years. He has also been world champion in junior and under-21 categories.

name: Lucie Ignace
biography: Lucie Ignace is a French karateka born December 16, 1992 in Saint-Denis, Réunion. She won the gold medal in the 55 kg category at the 2012 World Karate Championships in Paris after securing a bronze medal at the 2012 European Karate Championships in Tenerife. In June 2015, he competed in the inaugural European Games, for France in karate, more specifically, Women's Kumite for 61 kilograms. She earned a gold medal.

name: Alizee Agier
biography: Alizee Agier, born July 7, 1994 in Semur-en-Auxois, is a French karateka, member of the French team. She won the gold medal in the 68 kg category at the 2014 World Karate Championships in Bremen.

name: Alisa Buchinger
biography: Alisa Buchinger (26 October 1992 in Salzburg) is an Austrian Kumite Karateka. She is a multiple U-21 European champion and became the U-18 World Champion in 2009. At the 2016 World Cup in Linz she became world champion in the weight class up to 68 kg.

name: Elena Quirici
biography:
Elena Quirici (16 February 1994 in Schinznach-Dorf) is a Swiss Kumite Karateka. At the 2016 European Karate Championships in Montpellier, she won the gold medal in the under 68kg category, beating Austria's Alisa Buchinger in the final. She had previously finished second at the 2015 Karate European Championships in Istanbul after being beaten by the same Buchinger in the final. She is a gold medalist in individual kumite of less than 68 kg and kumite per team at the European Karate Championships 2018 with Noémie Kornfeld, Ramona Brüderlin and Nina Radjenovic.

She is a silver medalist under 68kg at the 2019 Karate European Championships in Guadalajara.

name: Iryna Zaretska
biography:
Iryna Zaretska (4 March 1996 in Ukraine) is a Ukrainian and Azerbaijani karateka. 
She won for Ukraine a bronze medal in kumite less than 68 kg at the 2014 Karate World Championships in Bremen, then for Azerbaijan the gold medal in the same category at the 2015 European Games in Baku and in team kumite at the 2016 European Karate Championships in Montpellier. 
She is a gold medalist at the 2017 Islamic Solidarity Games in Baku and a silver medalist at the 2018 Karate European Championships in Novi Sad. 
She was proclaimed World Champion in November 2018 in Madrid.

name: Ayumi Uekusa
biography: Ayumi Uekusa, born July 25, 1992, is a Japanesse karateka from Hachi-aki city in Chiba Prefecture. She won the gold medal in the 68 kg o more category at the 2016 World Karate Championships in Linz.

name: Eleni Chatziliadou
biography: Eleni Chatziliadou (born July 29, 1993) is a Greek karateka. In 2018, she won a gold medal at the World karate championships. The same year, she also won a silver medal for Greece, at the 2018 Mediterranean Games and at European karate championships.

name: Ryo Kiyuna
biography: Ryo Kiyuna born July 12, 1990, in Okinawa, Japan.  Disciple of the great master, Tsuguo Sakumoto (Three times Individual Kata World Champion). Ryo Kiyuna Is two times individual world champion, Bremen 2014 and Linz 2016.

name: Damian Quintero
biography: Damian Quintero was born on July 4, 1984 in Buenos Aires (Argentina). When He was 6 years old moved with his family to Torremolinos, Malaga (Spain). In individual and team category has several times won the gold medal in European championships. In Bremen in 2014 he achieved his greatest success, World Champion in teams category.

name: Minh Dack
biography: Vu Duc Minh Dack is a French karateka, kata specialist, born on October 18, 1982 in Noumea (New Caledonia).

name: Sandra Sanchez
biography: Sandra Sanchez is a spanish karateka, born on September 16, 1981 in Talavera de la Reina. At the age of 33 years in 2015, she participated for the first time in a European Championship winning the gold medal, that year participated in the first European Games in Baku also winning the gold medal. After 4 consecutive European Champions titles, she was proclaimed World Champion in Madrid 2018 at the age of 37 years.

name: Kiyou Shimizu
biography: Kiyou Shimizu born December 7, 1993, is a Japanese karateka, best known for winning the World Karate Championship 2014. Several similarities are noted with compatriot Rika Usami. They have both won the Asian Games and the World Championship. They won the competition by performing the same kata (Chatanyara Kushanku). And finally, they beat the same person in the finals, Sandy Scordo.

name: Sandy Scordo
biography: Sandy Scordo is a French karate, kata specialist, born on July 25, 1985 in Carpentras (France).

name: David Luque
biography: David Luque Camacho, born April 15, 1968, is a Spanish Karateka known to have won the World Championship title in individual kumite men under 60 kilos at the 1996 and 1998 Karate World Championships.

name: Damien Dovy
biography: Damien Dovy (born 31 March 1966 in Vitry-sur-Seine, France) is a French karateka who won multiple medals at Karate's top Competitions the European Karate Championships and World Karate Championships. Although born in France Dovy also represented Benin the country of his heritage at international level.

name: Alexandre Biamonti
biography: Alexandre Biamonti is a French karateka, born on February 30, 1973 in Marseille. He won 9 consecutive times the European Championship and the gold medal at the 1998 Karate World Championships in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.

name: Ivan Leal
biography: Iván Leal (Arganda del Rey, Madrid, Spain, September 18, 1978) is a Spanish karateka, world champion in kumite of less than 75 kg in 2000 and 2002, and by teams in 2002 and 2006. At the age of 7 competed For the first time in katas and to the 14 disputed its first Championship of Spain in kumite. With just 21 years he achieved his first European Championship and months later he won the World Championship, a title he revalidated two years later. After withdraw from the competition, He created his Club Ivan Leal gym, which is in the town of Arganda del Rey.

name: Wayne Otto
biography: Wayne Otto OBE (born May 18, 1966 in Hackney, London, United Kingdom) he is a British karateka. He has a 5th Dan black belt in karate and is the winner of multiple World Karate Championships and is in the Guinness World Records for winning the most Karate medals. In 2012 Wayne became the head coach of the Norwegian Karate Federation

name: Jose Manuel Egea
biography:
José Manuel Egea is a Spanish karateka, born on February 20, 1964. He won the world title record, winner in individual Kumite.
 He won three titles as world karate karate champion in 1988 (Sanbon category), 1990 (-80kg) and 1992 (-80kg). He also won six league titles in European karate in 1983 (Open category), 1985, 1986, 1988, 1989 and 1990 (all in-80kg).

name: Michaël Milon
biography: Michaël Milon, born on 3 March 1972 in Tours, is a French karate champion. He has been a three-time world champion in three-time World Cup winner, twelve times European champion, nine-time French champion and nine-time winner of the French Cup.

name: Antonio Diaz
biography: Antonio Diaz (Caracas, Venezuela, June 12, 1980) is a Venezuelan karateka twice world champion in kata (Belgrade 20102 and Paris 2012) . He also reached the gold medal at the World Games Duisburg 2005 and Cali 2013.

name: Luca Valdesi
biography: Luca Valdesi (born June 18, 1976, in Palermo, Italy) is a Karate world champion in both Team and Individual Kata events. Valdesi began his study of Karate at age six, under the guidance of his father Andrea, at several city gyms.

name: Tsuguo Sakumoto
biography:
Tsuguo Sakumoto, born on 13 December 1947 in  in the Okinawan village of Onna (Japan), is a Japanese legend in kata, by wining successive world championships with the kata Anan, he put the Okinawan family style of Ryuei-ryu karate on the international map.

He came to karate a little late, not starting karate training until he was fourteen. His first style was Goju-ryu karate.

The international world became aware of Tsuguo Sakumoto and his style of Ryuei-ryu when at the age of 37 he won the 7th Karate World Championship held in Maastrict, Holland. He performed the kata Anan, which many people outside of Okinawa and Japan had never really seen. The audience were thrilled by his powerfully dynamic yet graceful performances.
He went on to become a three-time world champion in kata, winning in 1984 (Maastrict), 1986 (Sydney) and 1988 (Cairo). He is also a two-time winner of the World Games (1985 and 1989) and a two-time winner of the World Cup(1987 and 1989).

Tsuguo Sakumoto is the master of world champions like Ryo Kiyuna.

name: Atsuko Wakai
biography: Atsuko Wakai (born September 12, 1971) is a Japanese practitioner of karate who has won many international and Japanese national competitions in kata, including unprecedented numbers of consecutive titles in World Karate Federation (WKF) and All Japan Karatedo championships. She holds the rank of 5th dan black belt from the Japan Karatedo Federation (JKF), training in Seigokan Goju-ryu karate.

name: Rika Usami
biography:
Rika Usami (宇佐美 里香, born February 20, 1986) is a Japanese practitioner in Shōrin-ryū Karate. She had said in an interview that she started karate when she was 10 years old by joining a Goju-ryu-style dojo located near her family’s house in Tokyo, after seeing a female fighter on television. Her older brother has been practicing karate to which he even let Usami wear his karate gi on occasions, so that helped her a lot when she decided to eventually start practicing Karate herself.

Her first karate tournament was when she was a green belt at 12 years old in elementary school. She didn't participate in big tournaments until at age 15. She first won a big tournament at 17 years old at the national high school championship.
